[2
Date: Sat, 18 Oct 1997
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: Kenya Television, KTN-TV, 16 Oct 1997

Assistant Minister of Health Basil Criticos reported on the Cholera
epidemic to the Kenya Parliament on 16 Oct.
Admissions to health centers 2500
Deaths 140
Funds committed to control 12.5 million shillings
The Ministry is seeking additional funds and is sending teams composed of
senior health officers into the areas affected. Critics said the situation
has grown worse in Migori, Migori, Rachuonyo, Suba, Homa Bay and Kisumu
[Western Kenya and has spread to the Molo division of Nakuru [Central Rift
Valley.
[ProMED-mail would very much like to hear some details from someone in
Kenya who can give any details on the epidemic (epidemic curve, etiologic
agent, attack rates, case fatality rates, geographic distribution) and
comment about control measures. -Mod. pc
